UID:980662
DESCRIPTION:<p>A <em>New York Times</em> Critics&rsquo\; Pick\, <em>Two St
 rangers (Carry a Cake Across New York)</em> &ldquo\;delivers lavishly on l
 aughter\, escape\, and fantasy.&rdquo\;<br /><br />Meet Dougal\, an imposs
 ibly upbeat Brit who has just landed in New York City for the first time t
 o attend the wedding of the father he&rsquo\;s never met. Meet Robin\, the
  sister of the bride and a no-nonsense New Yorker with a lot of errands to
  do for the bride&mdash\;including picking up the groom&rsquo\;s estranged
  son from the airport.<br /><br />These two strangers begin their journey 
 together navigating New York City\, secrets\, and second chances. <em>The 
 Boston Globe</em> proclaims\, it&rsquo\;s &ldquo\;Irresistible! Clever\, f
 unny\, and delightfully surprising!&rdquo\;<br /><br />&ldquo\;An efferves
 cent new musical comedy! Delivers lavishly on laughter\, escape\, and fant
 asy.&rdquo\; &mdash\; <em>The New York Times</em><br /><br />&ldquo\;It&rs
 quo\;s going to be stuck in your head for days. Absolutely charming.&rdquo
 \; &mdash\; Entertainment Weekly<br /><br />&ldquo\; Achieves something ma
 gical.&rdquo\; &mdash\; <em>Vulture</em></p>
LOCATION:Longacre Theatre\, 220 West 48th Street\, New York NY 10036
END:VEVENT
